  "narrative": "DRIVER\nUSD leads D1 CSM at 100 in a Risk-Off Medium regime, but the H4 CSM divergence is the dominant short-term signal: USD has faded to 0 on H4 while CHF surges to 100 and NZD to 82, making the D1 USD trend structurally intact but tactically exhausted intraday. GBPJPY at D1+H4 Strong Buy with GBPUSD correlation 0.89 is the cleanest expression of GBP momentum, while USDCAD D1+H4 Buy holds where the D1 USD trend still has traction. The CHF 100-point H4 acceleration against USD's zero H4 reading means USDCHF longs carry immediate reversal risk despite the D1 neutral-buy setup.\n\nMOMENTUM\nGaining: GBPJPY CMP 54 with H4 at 70 accelerating, GBPUSD H4 64 rising against D1 fade\nFading: EURUSD CMP 40 with D1 at 37 falling, NZDUSD CMP 47 with D1 at 45 declining\n\nWATCH\nUK fiscal data release hits GBPUSD directly; a negative print confirms the high-impact bearish UK theme and reverses the H4 GBP momentum rally.\nWTI Oil holding above 100 sustains CAD support; a break below 99 triggers USDCAD D1 Buy acceleration toward new highs.\nBoJ policy commentary targets USDJPY; a hold confirmation extends the D1 buy at 70 momentum and pulls CADJPY higher via its 0.69 correlation.",
